Redux

- Redux is a universal data storage
- A predictible state container for javscript applications
- Allows you to share the state between components
- Redux is a state management tool for javascript apps 
- It integrates nicely with React. can use it with any other view library. It allow us to track changing data.





why  use redux?

- when we have big complicated data for complex applications.
- Any component can pul any piece of data from the redux store. so data needs to be shared between multiple components
- helop syou write applications that behave consitently
- run in different environments(client, server, and native) and are easy to test
- Provides a greate developer experience. such as live code editing combined with a time traveling debugger

